This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and grammatical error detection. It could also belong to "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as it proposes a neural network-based approach. Additionally, it could be categorized under "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques for language processing. "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as it involves the use of neural networks. Finally, it could be categorized under "cs.CY" (Computers and Society) as it deals with the impact of technology on language and communication.
